<subSubSection id="90510FCC4FEADA47F1549AD3BFAEF7FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D5476302755CE0C8774B889260959D56" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="741519B2CC8CF7204691B46313B73BF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="8406EA67D11379F84322794AD13C01AA" authorityName="Campos-Filho, Araujo &amp; Taiti" authorityYear="2017" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Cylindroniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindroniscus flaviae" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviae">
<emphasis id="98531315BE2699B82E98A5A7825D5481" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Cylindroniscus flaviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows preference for organic matter deposits and highly humid areas in the aphotic zone (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D2ABF4A96D65CC1DED8AA21C1C0B3C26" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. A Gruta da Tapagem (Caverna do Diabo), Acungui geomorphological group B Cylindroniscus flaviae Campos-Filho, Araujo &amp; Taiti, 2017 foraging in the organic matter C surrounding area outside Gruta Toca Coroa do Frade, Casa Nova geomorphological group D aphotic zone of the Toca Coroa do Frade." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684900" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2B</figureCitation>
). The organic matter was observed in several conduits of the Gruta da Tapagem, always far from the touristic stretches, and it was composed of particulate vegetal debris or small tree branches. The environmental variables along the cave ranged from 19.9 °C to 20.4 °C and the relative air humidity from 95% to 99.1%. The individuals demonstrated sensitivity to the flash lights of the lanterns, always moving in opposite direction.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E55C6685BCF37B3A1F5A5820A019E9EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7D093BA9253E6E33105FD07890B446C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12CF7A068BAA17A3983CE710CB2848D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
This species is recorded from several caves in the 
<normalizedToken id="A859E79095A17BE24D2BA4365AB59175" originalValue="Açungui">Acungui</normalizedToken>
geomorphological group (see Campos-Filho et al. 2017).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
